(104, 2, '2015-11-03 20:37:32', '2015-11-03 20:37:32', '<strong>Put simply, life insurance is peace of mind.</strong> It is the assurance that things will be taken care of even after you are gone. Think of it as a safety net for everyone you care about.\r\n<h2>Life Insurance Basics</h2>\r\n<strong>Term life insurance</strong> is easy to understand. You pay a regular monthly fee for the duration of the term in return for which your beneficiary receives a lump sum payout on your passing. In most cases, this <strong>death benefit</strong> is tax free.\r\n<h2>What is it Good For?</h2>\r\n<strong>Basically, term life insurance is used to take care of the responsibilities you leave behind. </strong>It lets your beneficiary manage the things you would handle if you were able.  Most people use it for some or all of the following things:\r\n\r\n*Funerary expenses, estate taxes, and other end of life expenses\r\n\r\n*Spousal support and education for your children\r\n\r\n*Paying off any debts you might leave behind such as mortgages and student loans\r\n\r\n*Provide an inheritance for your heirs regardless of your assets\r\n<h2>What isn''t it Good For?</h2>\r\nWhile a term life insurance policy offers a great deal of benefits, it is not a single solution for every possible end of life situation. Carpenters cannot fix everything with a hammer, so why should a term life insurance policy resolve every end of life issue? Here are some things you should not use one for:\r\n\r\n*Do not use it as a substitute for a comprehensive retirement plan\r\n\r\n*Do not rely on it to cover long-term medical and care expenses\r\n\r\n*Do not consider it an investment\r\n<h2>What About Costs?</h2>\r\nA simple term life insurance policy is very affordable, <strong>in most cases it can cost less than three or four hundred dollars a year.</strong>\r\n\r\n*It''s about a third of the average monthly cable bill\r\n\r\n*It''s about a quarter of the average monthly cell phone bill\r\n\r\n*It''s a small fraction of the average monthly health insurance bill\r\n<h2>Picking the Right Life Insurance Policy</h2>\r\nThe most important thing to remember about life insurance is that <strong>no one policy fits everyone. </strong>Most people can do just fine with a simple term life insurance policy, but if you need more, there are more complex plans available that can cover a wide variety of factors including:\r\n\r\n*Estate Planning\r\n\r\n*Minimizing Tax Expenses\r\n\r\n*Providing for Charitable Donations\r\n<div>Find the policy that''s right for you, and don''t be afraid to change it when your needs change.</div>', 'Life Insurance Guide (Part I) - Life Insurance Basics', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'what-is-life-insurance', '', '', '2015-11-06 05:59:49', '2015-11-06 05:59:49', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8771/nia/?p=104', 0, 'post', '', 1),
