(123, 2, '2015-11-06 20:30:36', '2015-11-06 20:30:36', 'The key to <strong>permanent life insurance</strong> is that you trade off the <strong>simplicity</strong> of <strong>term life insurance</strong> for the  <strong>flexibility</strong> of something more permanent.\r\n\r\nThis very flexibility means that there is more than one kind of permanent life insurance. You can buy <strong>whole life insurance</strong>, <strong>universal life insurance</strong>, and even <strong>variable life insurance</strong>. Each kind fits a different spectrum of customer need.\r\n<h2>Common Features of Permanent Life Insurance</h2>\r\nEach of the different kinds of permanent life insurance has at least two features in common. First, they all have a <strong>cash value</strong>, and second, none of them have a <strong>fixed term</strong>.\r\n<h4>Whole Life Insurance</h4>\r\nThe simplest form of permanent life insurance is <strong>whole life insurance</strong>. Its biggest advantage is its stability. Your premiums are fixed, as is the rate at which your <strong>cash value</strong> grows. It doesn''t grow very fast, but it always grows. It''s a very good choice for risk-averse policy holders.\r\n<h4>Variable Life Insurance</h4>\r\nWith <strong>variable life insurance</strong>, you can trade some of that stability for a greater potential reward.  As with <strong>whole life insurance</strong>, you pay a fixed premium. However, the <strong>cash value</strong> is calculated differently. Rather than simply growing at a low fixed rate, your cash value is placed in the insurance company''s investment portfolio.\r\n\r\nThis has both advantages and disadvantages.\r\n\r\n<ul class="listcontent">\r\n<li>The biggest advantage is <strong>growth</strong>: if the company invests well, your cash value can grow much faster than with a whole life insurance policy.</li>\r\n<li>The disadvantage is <strong>risk</strong>: by tying your cash value to the company''s investments, you share in both their profits and losses.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4>Universal Life Insurance</h4>\r\nThe third kind, <strong>universal life insurance</strong>, gives you control. With a universal policy, you can adjust both your premium and your benefit amount. You can even use your cash value to either pay off or reduce your premiums.\r\n\r\nThe trade-off is that in order to gain control in one area, you have to give up control in another. In this case, it''s rate of growth. With universal life insurance your cash value increases at a variable rate set by the insurance company.\r\n<h4>Variable Universal Life Insurance</h4>\r\nThe fourth kind, <strong>variable universal life insurance</strong>, takes elements of both universal and variable policies and combines them into one.\r\n\r\n<strong>Like a universal policy</strong>, it gives you control of your premiums and benefit. You can adjust either, and trade in cash value to reduce or pay off your existing premiums.\r\n\r\n<strong>Like a variable policy</strong>, you tie your cash value to the insurance company''s own investments, letting it rise and fall with them. It offers some risk, but also potential for growth.\r\n<h2>Choosing Between Types</h2>\r\nWhich type you choose, depends on your needs and your tolerance for risk.\r\n\r\n<ul class="listcontent">\r\n<li>If you are risk averse and don''t mind a relatively low rate of growth, a <strong>whole life policy</strong> may be your best choice.</li>\r\n<li>If you are willing to accept more risk for a potentially greater payoff, then consider a <strong>variable life policy</strong>.</li>\r\n<li>If you want a more hands-on approach, you can take control with a <strong>universal life policy</strong>.</li>\r\n<li>If you want the hands on approach, and don''t mind accepting a little risk for potentially greater reward, then try a <strong>variable universal life policy</strong>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\nRemember, there''s always a policy for everyone. You just have to know your needs.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Life Insurance Guide (Part IV) - Permanent Life Insurance', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'life-insurance-guide-part-iv-permanent-life-insurance', '', '', '2015-11-07 16:53:31', '2015-11-07 16:53:31', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8771/nia/?p=123', 0, 'post', '', 0),
